We had such an awesome time throwing down all this crunchy DnB - that we've decided to release our live set recording! 

Wizards of Kingston Events have a warm place in our hearts. We first met behind the decks (literally between our sets on the Main Stage!) at a previous Spring Camp Out - where Swim Inc played after Emmotica. So it's very special for us to be back where we first met, and to share with you our DnB collab project - Crunch Factor. 

Thank you to everyone who came to dance with us, we can't wait for another good stomp soon!

Our 39th guest mix episode comes from SL Small, otherwise known under the Drum & Bass alias Vandermou. Born in Seville (Spain), this producer began to enter on the world of broken rhythms at a very young age. His first contacts were at raves in the area back in 2007 where he fell in love with the style and decided to form his first group called Diversity. A group with which, for several years, he produced several re-rubs recognized by the public, performed in some venues in the capital and shared a line up with international artists such as Rennie Pilgrem and Atomic Hooligan.

After making a name for himself on the national Drum & Bass scene since 2014, he decided in 2018 to restart his career in the style that he is most passionate about and started the SL Small project, debuting with General Midi at Sala Prisma and performing in Bristol (Southside Breaks and Wharf Recordings) sharing line up with ED209 and Borai.

Thanks to his years on the scene, you can find songs from 2007 onwards in his sets, focusing on tech break, electro break and psy break sounds. In 2022 his first own track came out on the English record label Wharf Recordings and at the beginning of 2023 he released his first EP on Creative Sound Records, managing to sneak TOP 28 of the TOP 100 Beatport Breakbeat New Releases.

‚ÄúThe term "boom bap" is an onomatopoeia that represents the sounds used for the bass (kick) drum and snare drum, respectively. The style is usually recognized by a main drum loop that uses a hard-hitting, acoustic bass drum sample on the downbeats, a snappy acoustic snare drum sample on the upbeats, and an "in your face" audio mix emphasizing the drum loop, and the kick-snare combination in particular.‚Äù - Simon Reynolds, 2009.
